---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import LangSwitcher from '../components/LangSwitcher.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---

<Base title="Il Progetto — Race Database by Bonvi">
<div class="page-layout">

  <div class="sidebar-overlay" id="sidebar-overlay"></div>

  <aside class="sidebar" id="sidebar">
    <div class="sidebar-inner">
      <div class="brand">
        <div class="brand-mark">BRD</div>
        <div>
          <div class="brand-name">Race Database</div>
          <div class="brand-sub">Easy</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <nav class="sidebar-nav">
        <a href={`${base}/`} class="nav-btn">Prossime Gare</a>
        <a href={`${base}/archivio`} class="nav-btn">Archivio</a>
        <a href={`${base}/bmap`} class="nav-btn">BMAP</a>
        <a href={`${base}/progetto`} class="nav-btn active">Il Progetto</a>
        <a href={`${base}/faq`} class="nav-btn">FAQ</a>
        <a href={`${base}/contattami`} class="nav-btn">Contattami</a>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </aside>

  <main class="main">

    <div class="mobile-topbar">
      <button class="mobile-menu-btn" id="menu-btn" aria-label="Apri menu">☰</button>
      <LangSwitcher />
    </div>

    <div class="page-content">

      <header class="page-header">
        <div class="page-tag">About</div>
        <h1 class="page-title" data-i18n="title">Il Progetto</h1>
        <p class="page-lead" data-i18n="lead">Un archivio digitale di gare ciclistiche — per esplorare percorsi nel dettaglio, conoscere ogni salita e "vedere" la strada prima ancora di percorrerla.</p>
      </header>

      <section class="section">
        <h2 class="section-title" data-i18n="who_title">Chi c'è dietro</h2>
        <p data-i18n="who_p1">
          Mi chiamo Andrea Bonvicin, sono preparatore atletico e sport scientist. Lavoro con ciclisti di diverse categorie e da sempre ho avuto una passione per i percorsi: sapere dove si trova ogni strappo, conoscere il fondo stradale, capire il profilo prima di arrivarci.
        </p>
        <p id="who_p2_el">
          L'idea è nata da una mancanza concreta: per le categorie Elite e Pro esiste già di tutto, ma per il ciclismo giovanile — Allievi/e e Junior soprattutto — non c'è praticamente nulla di organizzato. Niente mappe, niente profili, niente a cui fare riferimento per preparare una gara. Ho iniziato a raccogliere i file GPX per colmare questo vuoto, e col tempo è diventato un archivio vero e proprio. Se vuoi contribuire aggiungendo una gara, trovi tutto nella pagina <a href={`${base}/contattami`}>Contattami</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2 class="section-title" data-i18n="what_title">Cosa trovi qui</h2>
        <div class="features-grid">
          <div class="feature-card">
            <div class="feature-icon">◈</div>
            <div class="feature-title" data-i18n="f1_title">Mappa interattiva</div>
            <p class="feature-desc" data-i18n="f1_desc">Il tracciato GPX disegnato sulla mappa con partenza e arrivo segnati. Zoomabile ed esplorabile.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-card">
            <div class="feature-icon">△</div>
            <div class="feature-title" data-i18n="f2_title">Profilo altimetrico 3D</div>
            <p class="feature-desc" data-i18n="f2_desc">Il grafico dell'altitudine con rendering tridimensionale e gradiente colorato in base alla pendenza.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-card">
            <div class="feature-icon">⊘</div>
            <div class="feature-title" data-i18n="f3_title">Salite rilevate</div>
            <p class="feature-desc" data-i18n="f3_desc">Ogni salita significativa viene rilevata automaticamente dal GPX e classificata per difficoltà, lunghezza e pendenza media.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-card">
            <div class="feature-icon">◉</div>
            <div class="feature-title" data-i18n="f4_title">Street View</div>
            <p class="feature-desc" data-i18n="f4_desc">Un link diretto a Google Street View posizionato all'inizio di ogni salita. Puoi esplorare virtualmente il percorso prima di arrivarci.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="example-note" data-i18n="example_note">
          ↑ Mappa · Profilo 3D · Salite rilevate · Street View — tutto da un singolo file GPX
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2 class="section-title" data-i18n="support_title">Sostieni il progetto</h2>
        <p data-i18n="support_p1">
          Questo archivio è gratuito, senza pubblicità e mantenuto nel tempo libero. Aggiungere gare, mantenere il server, migliorare il visualizzatore — tutto ha un costo. Se lo trovi utile e vuoi contribuire, puoi offrire un caffè su Ko-fi. Non è obbligatorio, ma fa sempre piacere.
        </p>
        <p data-i18n="support_p2">
          In futuro, con un po' di supporto, sarebbe bello poter integrare Street View direttamente nella pagina — senza aprire una nuova scheda — usando le API ufficiali Google. Per ora il link funziona egregiamente, ma è uno degli obiettivi.
        </p>
        <div class="kofi-wrap">
          <a href="https://ko-fi.com/andreabonvicin" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="kofi-btn">
            <span class="kofi-icon">☕</span>
            <span data-i18n="kofi_btn">Offrimi un caffè su Ko-fi</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section section-cta">
        <a href={`${base}/`} class="cta-btn" data-i18n="cta_explore">Esplora il database →</a>
        <a href={`${base}/contattami`} class="cta-btn cta-secondary" data-i18n="cta_contact">Contattami</a>
        <a href="https://ko-fi.com/andreabonvicin" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="cta-btn cta-kofi">☕ <span data-i18n="cta_support">Sostieni</span></a>
      </section>

    </div>
  </main>

  <footer>
    <a href="https://linktr.ee/bonvicin.coaching" target="_blank">
      &copy; 2026 Andrea Bonvicin — BRD Race Database — Licenza AGPL v3
    </a>
  </footer>

</div>
</Base>

<script define:vars={{ base }}>
  const menuBtn = document.getElementById('menu-btn');
  const overlay = document.getElementById('sidebar-overlay');
  const sidebar = document.getElementById('sidebar');

  function openDrawer() { sidebar.classList.add('open'); overlay.classList.add('open'); document.body.style.overflow = 'hidden'; }
  function closeDrawer() { sidebar.classList.remove('open'); overlay.classList.remove('open'); document.body.style.overflow = ''; }

  menuBtn?.addEventListener('click', openDrawer);
  overlay?.addEventListener('click', closeDrawer);
  document.querySelectorAll('.nav-btn').forEach(btn => btn.addEventListener('click', closeDrawer));

  // i18n
  const lang = localStorage.getItem('brd-lang') || 'it';
  if (lang === 'en') {
    const t = {
      title: 'The Project',
      lead: 'A digital archive of cycling races — to explore routes in detail, discover every climb and "see" the road before you even ride it.',
      who_title: "Who's behind it",
      who_p1: "My name is Andrea Bonvicin, I'm an athletic trainer and sport scientist. I work with cyclists across different categories and have always had a passion for routes: knowing where every steep section is, what the road surface is like, understanding the profile before getting there.",
      what_title: 'What you find here',
      f1_title: 'Interactive map',
      f1_desc: 'The GPX track drawn on the map with start and finish marked. Zoomable and explorable.',
      f2_title: '3D elevation profile',
      f2_desc: 'The altitude chart with three-dimensional rendering and a colour gradient based on gradient.',
      f3_title: 'Detected climbs',
      f3_desc: 'Every significant climb is automatically detected from the GPX and classified by difficulty, length and average gradient.',
      f4_title: 'Street View',
      f4_desc: 'A direct link to Google Street View positioned at the start of each climb. You can virtually explore the route before you get there.',
      example_note: '↑ Map · 3D profile · Detected climbs · Street View — all from a single GPX file',
      support_title: 'Support the project',
      support_p1: 'This archive is free, ad-free and maintained in my spare time. Adding races, maintaining the server, improving the visualiser — everything has a cost. If you find it useful and want to contribute, you can buy me a coffee on Ko-fi. It\'s not required, but it\'s always appreciated.',
      support_p2: 'In the future, with a bit of support, it would be great to integrate Street View directly into the page — without opening a new tab — using the official Google APIs. For now the link works perfectly, but that\'s one of the goals.',
      kofi_btn: 'Buy me a coffee on Ko-fi',
      cta_explore: 'Explore the database →',
      cta_contact: 'Contact me',
      cta_support: 'Support',
    };
    document.querySelectorAll('[data-i18n]').forEach(el => {
      const key = el.dataset.i18n;
      if (t[key]) el.textContent = t[key];
    });
    // who_p2 has a link inside — handle separately
    const p2 = document.getElementById('who_p2_el');
    if (p2) p2.innerHTML = `The idea came from a concrete gap: for Elite and Pro categories there's already everything online, but for youth cycling — especially U16 and Junior — there's practically nothing organised. No maps, no profiles, nothing to reference when preparing for a race. I started collecting GPX files to fill this gap, and over time it became a proper archive. If you want to contribute by adding a race, you'll find everything on the <a href="${base}/contattami">Contact me</a> page.`;
  }
</script>

<style>
  .page-layout {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 250px 1fr;
    grid-template-rows: 1fr auto;
    min-height: 100vh;
  }

  .sidebar-overlay {
    display: none;
    position: fixed; inset: 0;
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.45);
    z-index: 99;
    backdrop-filter: blur(2px);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(2px);
  }
  .sidebar-overlay.open { display: block; }

  .sidebar {
    background: var(--bg2);
    border-right: 1px solid var(--border);
    position: sticky; top: 0;
    height: 100vh; overflow-y: auto;
    grid-row: 1 / 2;
  }

  .sidebar-inner { display: flex; flex-direction: column; padding: 1.75rem 1.25rem; height: 100%; gap: 1.5rem; }

  .brand { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.85rem; padding-bottom: 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .brand-mark { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: 0.08em; background: var(--text); color: var(--bg); padding: 0.3rem 0.5rem; border-radius: 2px; flex-shrink: 0; }
  .brand-name { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.02em; line-height: 1.1; }
  .brand-sub { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.6rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.12em; color: var(--text3); margin-top: 0.15rem; }

  .sidebar-nav { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.4rem; }
  .nav-btn { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.72rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: var(--text2); text-decoration: none; padding: 0.6rem 0.75rem; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 3px; background: transparent; transition: all 0.15s; display: block; }
  .nav-btn:hover { color: var(--text); border-color: var(--text2); background: var(--bg3); }
  .nav-btn.active { color: var(--accent); border-color: var(--accent); background: rgba(212, 64, 26, 0.05); }

  /* ── Mobile topbar ── */
  .mobile-topbar { display: none; }
  .mobile-menu-btn { background: none; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 3px; cursor: pointer; padding: 0.4rem 0.65rem; font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--text); line-height: 1; transition: border-color 0.15s; }
  .mobile-menu-btn:hover { border-color: var(--text2); }

  .main { padding: 3rem 3.5rem; max-width: 780px; }
  .page-content { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 3rem; }

  .page-header { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); padding-bottom: 2rem; }
  .page-tag { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.62rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.15em; color: var(--accent); margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .page-title { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 2.8rem; font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: 0.01em; line-height: 1; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: var(--text); }
  .page-lead { font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--text2); line-height: 1.6; max-width: 560px; }

  .section { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem; }
  .section-title { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 1.3rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.03em; color: var(--text); padding-bottom: 0.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .section p { font-size: 0.93rem; line-height: 1.75; color: var(--text2); }
  .section p a { color: var(--accent); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 3px; }

  .features-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1rem; }
  .feature-card { border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 4px; padding: 1.25rem; background: var(--bg2); }
  .feature-icon { font-size: 1.2rem; color: var(--accent); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .feature-title { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.03em; margin-bottom: 0.4rem; }
  .feature-desc { font-size: 0.82rem; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--text2); }

  .example-note { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.65rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: var(--text3); padding: 0.6rem 1.25rem; background: var(--bg3); border-top: 1px solid var(--border); }

  .section-cta { flex-direction: row; gap: 0.75rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); }

  .cta-btn { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.72rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; padding: 0.75rem 1.25rem; border-radius: 3px; text-decoration: none; transition: all 0.15s; background: var(--text); color: var(--bg); border: 1px solid var(--text); }
  .cta-btn:hover { background: var(--accent); border-color: var(--accent); }
  .cta-secondary { background: transparent; color: var(--text); border: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .cta-secondary:hover { background: var(--bg3); border-color: var(--text2); color: var(--text); }
  .cta-kofi { background: #FF5E5B; color: #fff; border-color: #FF5E5B; }
  .cta-kofi:hover { background: #e54c49; border-color: #e54c49; color: #fff; }

  .kofi-wrap { padding-top: 0.5rem; }
  .kofi-btn { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.6rem; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.72rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; padding: 0.8rem 1.5rem; border-radius: 3px; text-decoration: none; background: #FF5E5B; color: #fff; border: 1px solid #FF5E5B; transition: all 0.15s; }
  .kofi-btn:hover { background: #e54c49; border-color: #e54c49; }
  .kofi-icon { font-size: 1rem; }

  footer { grid-column: 1 / -1; grid-row: 2; text-align: center; padding: 1rem 1.25rem; background: var(--bg2); color: var(--text2); font-size: 0.8rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); flex-shrink: 0; }
  footer a { color: var(--text2); text-decoration: none; font-weight: 500; transition: color 0.2s; }
  footer a:hover { color: var(--accent); }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .page-layout { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }

    .mobile-topbar { display: flex; align-items: center; padding: 0.75rem 1rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); background: var(--bg); position: sticky; top: 0; z-index: 10; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }

    .sidebar {
      position: fixed !important;
      top: 0; left: 0;
      height: 100dvh !important;
      width: 285px;
      z-index: 100;
      transform: translateX(-100%);
      box-shadow: none;
      overflow-y: auto;
    }
    .sidebar.open { transform: translateX(0); box-shadow: 4px 0 32px rgba(0,0,0,0.18); }
    .sidebar-inner { height: auto; min-height: 100%; padding-bottom: calc(1.25rem + env(safe-area-inset-bottom, 1rem)); }

    .main { padding: 0 1rem calc(1.5rem + env(safe-area-inset-bottom, 0.5rem)); }
    .page-title { font-size: 2rem; }
    .features-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .section-cta { flex-wrap: wrap; }
  }
</style>